<h2 class="western" style="page-break-after: avoid;"><font
size="6">Understanding SATRN</font></h2>

<p style="text-indent: 0.5in;">The Situational Awareness
Tactical Response Network (SATRN) is an
operator-in-the-loop training environment which enables
both our Department of Defense (DoD) stakeholders and
industry to measure and adjust Tactics, Techniques &
Procedures (TTP) to ensure the warfighter gets the most
effective and reliable tools in the field. It also allows
force-effectiveness analysis for differing weapons systems
as well as the Threat Evaluation and Weapon Assignment
(TEWA) algorithms that are employed to manage the
battlespace. Finally SATRN provides an end-to-end
environment for best-of-breed product testing. This allows
Lockheed Martin Missiles & Fire Control (MFC) to set up
conditions as they would appear in the field and introduce
small, incremental changes to show rapid deployment
solutions to today's issues.</p>

<p></p>

